<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,901,1687]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,901,927]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Size. Length, male, 
<quantity box="[537,703,901,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.065" metricValueMax="3.32" metricValueMin="2.81" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.065" valueMax="3.32" valueMin="2.81">2.81–3.32mm</quantity>
; female, 
<quantity box="[817,984,901,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.035" metricValueMax="3.26" metricValueMin="2.81" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.035" valueMax="3.26" valueMin="2.81">2.81–3.26mm</quantity>
. Width, male, 
<quantity box="[1166,1332,901,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.885" metricValueMax="2.08" metricValueMin="1.69" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.885" valueMax="2.08" valueMin="1.69">1.69–2.08mm</quantity>
; female, 
<quantity box="[151,317,941,967]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.97" metricValueMin="1.63" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.7999999999999998" valueMax="1.97" valueMin="1.63">1.63–1.97mm</quantity>
. Pronotum with few very small or no distinct punctures; weakly cordate with dense, erect, apically recurved, moderately long scales condensed along anterolateral margins and in paramedian clumps in apical half of length. Elytra rounded, with similar apically recurved scales linearly arranged along intervals, strial regions with very fine, appressed, elongate, hair-like scales. Striae not impressed. Posterolateral area with series of 3–6 shallow, contiguous punctures. Mesosternum flat, slightly sloping anteriad, punctate to various extent in transverse band at extreme apex (usually obscured by prosternum). Male tergite VIII emarginate in middle. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[461,562,1181,1207]" captionStart="FIGURES 178–180" captionStartId="109.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[244,1340,1110,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-64@109.[240,1346,1098,1956]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 178–180. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, Theognete tzotzil species group. 178. T. huitepec. 179. T. tzotzil. 180. T. braunae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316700/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 179</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,901,1687]" box="[198,756,1221,1247]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,523,1221,1247]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[538,627,1221,1247]" name="Mexico" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">México</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[643,744,1221,1247]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,901,1687]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,390,1261,1287]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Natural history</emphasis>
. Collected from berlese extraction of cloud forest and oak-pine forest leaf litter at elevations of from 
<quantity box="[311,469,1301,1327]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6625" metricValueMax="1.825" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="1662.5" valueMax="1825.0" valueMin="1500.0">1500–1825m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,901,1687]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,540,1341,1367]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Derivation of specific name</emphasis>
. Noun in apposition; after the Tzotzil, the native Indians of the highlands of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,249,1381,1407]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
